# Catherine McGraw Portfolio

This is a personal portfolio website built with semantic HTML and custom SCSS using BEM naming conventions. It is fully responsive, accessible, and deployable to GitHub Pages.

---

## 📁 Project Structure

```
project-root/
├── index.html              # Main HTML file
├── dist/
│   └── style.css           # Compiled CSS output
├── src/
│   ├── main.scss           # SCSS entry point
│   ├── base/
│   │   ├── _variables.scss
│   │   └── _mixins.scss
│   └── components/
│       ├── _navbar.scss
│       ├── _card.scss
│       ├── _grid.scss
│       ├── _button.scss
│       └── _footer.scss
├── images/                 # Headshot, project images, etc.
├── package.json            # NPM setup
└── README.md               # This file
```

---

## 🛠️ Build Instructions

### 1. Install Dependencies
```bash
npm install
```

### 2. Build SCSS
```bash
npm run build
```

### 3. Watch for Changes
```bash
npm run watch
```

Make sure your Sass files compile into `dist/style.css` correctly.

---

## ♿ Accessibility

This project is built to meet [WCAG 2.1 A and AA](https://www.w3.org/WAI/WCAG21/quickref/) standards:

- Keyboard navigable
- Skip to content link
- Semantic headings and landmark roles
- Sufficient color contrast and alt text
- No keyboard traps

---

## 🚀 Deployment

To deploy to GitHub Pages:

1. Push to your GitHub repo
2. Go to Settings > Pages
3. Set source to your root or `/docs` folder
4. Ensure `index.html` and `dist/style.css` are committed

